    {
      "parameters": {
        "language": "javaScript",
        "jsCode": "const data = items[0].json;\nconst articles = data.articles;\nif (!articles || articles.length === 0) return [];\n\nconst BATCH_SIZE = 20;\n\nconst byUser = {};\nfor (const a of articles) {\n  if (!byUser[a.user_id]) {\n    byUser[a.user_id] = { user_id: a.user_id, scoring_prompt: a.scoring_prompt, articles: [] };\n  }\n  byUser[a.user_id].articles.push(a);\n}\n\nconst result = [];\nfor (const group of Object.values(byUser)) {\n  const batch = group.articles.slice(0, BATCH_SIZE);\n  result.push({\n    json: {\n      user_id: group.user_id,\n      scoring_prompt: group.scoring_prompt,\n      article_count: batch.length,\n      // JSON array input \u2014 qwen coder handles structured data better than text lines\n      articles_json: JSON.stringify(batch.map(a => ({\n        article_id: a.article_id,\n        title: a.title,\n        description: (a.description || '').slice(0, 150),\n      }))),\n    }\n  });\n}\nreturn result;"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        672,
        336
      ],
      "id": "code-batch-prompt",
      "name": "Batch Prompt Builder"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "You are a JSON transformation function. Input: array of news article objects. Output: array of scored objects.\n\nDO NOT explain. DO NOT refuse. DO NOT add commentary. Output ONLY the JSON array.\n\nINPUT articles:\n{{ $json.articles_json }}\n\nOUTPUT format \u2014 one object per input article:\n[\n  {\"article_id\": <copy from input>, \"user_id\": {{ $json.user_id }}, \"score\": <integer 1-100>, \"reason\": \"<max 20 words>\", \"category\": \"<from allowed list>\", \"decay\": \"<fast|moderate|slow>\"},\n  ...\n]\n\nSCORING CRITERIA (score each article's title and description using these rules):\n{{ $json.scoring_prompt }}\n\nDECAY:\nfast     = stale within 24h (breaking news, sports results, market moves, live events)\nmoderate = relevant 2-4 days (developing stories, earnings, short-term policy)\nslow     = valid weeks+ (research findings, policy analysis, product launches, explainers)\n\nALLOWED CATEGORIES (copy exactly):\nWorld News, Politics & Policy, Business & Finance, Technology, AI & Automation, Science & Health, Consumer & Gadgets, Entertainment & Celebrity, Lifestyle & Wellness, Sport, Crime & Justice, Weird & Viral, Opinion & Analysis, Other\n\nOutput the JSON array now ({{ $json.article_count }} objects, one per article):",
        "batching": {
          "batchSize": 1
        }
      },
